---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import hero from "/public/about_hero.jpg";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Pennine Digital - About">
  <section class="bg-light pb-24 relative h-[70vh] mt-20">
    <img src={hero.src} alt="Image of moorland" class="w-full h-full object-cover absolute" />

    <div class="absolute inset-0 h-full bg-black/45"></div>

    <div class="px-6 pt-20 h-full max-w-2xl mx-auto z-10 relative flex flex-col justify-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-semibold text-light">About Pennine Digital</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-light/90">
        Pennine Digital is a small web studio based in West Yorkshire, creating clean, modern websites for local businesses. The goal is
        straightforward — take the stress out of getting online and build something that actually helps.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pt-24 bg-light">
    <div class="px-6 md:max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading">The person behind the work</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-dark/80">
        I’m Chris — a front‑end developer and creative technologist based in Riddlesden. Over the last couple of years I’ve been learning
        modern development, building projects, and finding a way of working that feels calm, clear, and dependable.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-dark/80">
        Before getting into development, I spent years in hospitality. It taught me how to communicate well, stay organised, and look after
        people — skills that matter just as much in web design as writing code.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-dark/80">
        Pennine Digital is where those experiences meet: thoughtful design, modern code, and a friendly, no‑nonsense approach.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-28 bg-light">
    <div class="px-6 text-center max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading">What I care about</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-12 mt-8">
        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold">Clarity</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-dark/70">Everything is explained in plain language. No jargon, no confusion.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold">Reliability</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-dark/70">If I say I’ll do something, I do it. Simple as that.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold">Craftsmanship</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-dark/70">Websites should feel calm, fast, and well‑made — not rushed or overcomplicated.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-gradient-soft">
    <div class="px-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl">Why I started Pennine Digital</h2>
      <p class="text-dark/80 mt-4">
        The more I learned about the web, the more I saw how many local businesses were caught between pricey agencies and DIY builders that
        never quite hit the mark. I wanted to offer something in the middle — a personal, reliable service that builds websites from scratch
        and gives people something that actually feels right for their business.
      </p>
      <p class="text-dark/80 mt-2">
        That’s what Pennine Digital is about: a small, local studio with a straightforward, honest way of working.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center py-24">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-heading text-dark/80 mb-14">If you’d like to chat about a project, I’m here to help.</h2>
      <Button href="/contact" title="Get in touch" variant="light" />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
